  "body": "Two changes to make the `flake-go` workflow produce better signal when something hangs or flakes at low rates.\n\n**Job timeout (20m \u2192 25m).** The Go-level `-timeout 20m` baked into `make test` (`Makefile:1428`) currently raced the runner's 20m hard-kill, so a hanging test got SIGTERM'd by Actions instead of SIGQUIT'd by Go, and we never got the goroutine dump. Bumping the workflow job to 25m mirrors the layering already used by `test-go-pg` in `ci.yaml:409` and gives Go's timeout the 5m head start it expects.\n\n**Test count (25 \u2192 35).** Catches lower-frequency flakes that 25 attempts miss too often. For a 5% per-run flake, detection probability goes from ~72% at n=25 to ~83% at n=35; for 1\u20132% flakes the lift is larger. The longest successful flake-go run to date was 11m49s at n=25, so n=35 should peak around ~16\u201317m and stay well inside the new 25m budget.\n",
  "changed_files": 1,
